# elizaos/elizaos.github.io Daily Update (Dec 18, 2025)
## OVERVIEW 
Today's development focused on enhancing user interaction and configuration flexibility, including a new profile data export feature and improved site name management.

## KEY TECHNICAL DEVELOPMENTS

### Enhanced User Profile Functionality
A new feature was added to allow users to copy their profile data to LLMs, improving data portability and interaction. The site name was also updated from "Contributor Analytics" to "HiScores." ([#183](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/183))

### Streamlined Configuration Management
The site's `SITE_NAME` can now be configured directly from the pipeline config file, removing the dependency on GitHub secrets and simplifying setup for forks. ([#182](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/182))

### Repository Cleanup
Various development-related files and directories were cleaned up, contributing to a more organized and efficient codebase. ([#181](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/181))

## NEWLY OPENED PULL REQUESTS
No new pull requests were opened today.

## CLOSED ISSUES
No issues were closed today.

## NEW ISSUES
No new issues were reported today.

## ACTIVE ISSUES
No active issues with more than 3 comments.
